reviews.text: Many many coffee shops here with delicious outlets, this is an old estate which results in many styles and cuisines. It is convenient for the elderly as everything is under one place. There is also ntuc for the daily essentials. Place is mostly flat so it's easy for wheel chairs and the market trolley.

There is a NTUC and Sheng Siong Supermarket. Both are open 24 hours. There is a number of coffeeshops in this neighbourhood centre and some are also opened 24/7. There is a CK outlet here too so people can get their tolietries at attractive prices. There are also a few bubble tea outlets here for those who wish to settle their boba cravings. In the morning there are stalls selling fresh fish and vegetables also.

It's  a popular Makan Zone with more
than six coffee houses: offerings the
Local Evergreen Foods:  Cai Png,
Hainanese Chicken Rice, Fried Noodles,
[with tops of eggs, sausages, Fish-Cakes,
Fish Balls, Vegetables], Bak Choy Mee,
Duck Rice. Siew Yoke, Roast Pork, Nasi
Padang, Roti Prata, etc: Brands names such
as NTUC Supermarket [Blk 849] CK Departmental Store, MacDonalds
[Blk 846], Clinics, Community Centres
and Ageing Centres.
The place with a lots of good food, the Chu cha, fried Mee hoon, roasted chicken, duck noodles and duck rice are nice...
A lot of activities going on, you can find food, household items, fruits etc. There's a big space that holds events like night markets and pets carnivals sometimes.
